.TH LPF-EXPLAIN 8 "June 2026" "lpf 0.1.0-dev" "lpf Manual"
.SH NAME
lpf\-explain \- explain why a hypothetical packet passes or drops
.SH SYNOPSIS
lpf explain from <addr> to <addr> proto <proto> port <port>
.SH DESCRIPTION
Explain how a hypothetical packet would be handled by policy.
Results include decision, policy rule, NAT, route, queue, log, and state behavior.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\-\-json
emit machine\-readable explanation
.SH EXAMPLES
lpf explain from 10.0.0.5 to 1.1.1.1 proto tcp port 443
.SH FILES
/etc/lpf.conf
.SH SAFETY NOTES
Explain is advisory until compared with installed backend state.
.SH EXIT STATUS
0 on success.
Non\-zero when validation, planning, or host operations fail.
.SH SEE ALSO
lpf\-test(8), lpf\-rules(8)
